This paper deals with epistemic model checking, which involves reasoning about knowledge and belief of multiple agents. This is a topic that falls under the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses optimization techniques, which could be relevant to the sub-field of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of modal logic suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-field of programming languages (cs.PL).
